>&gt; stacks. What are you doing, exactly, to hit this?<br /><br />The reason I ask is that the _sane_ thing to do - if we really care<br />about this - is to change the 'vm_next' singly-linked list into using<br />'list.h'. It would clean up a fair amount of stuff, like removing the<br />need for that disgusting 'find_vma_prev()' thing. There are actually<br />several users of vma's that want to look at the previous vma, but<br />because it's hard to get at, they do something non-intuitive or odd.<br /><br />At the same time, we've had that vm_next pointer since pretty much day<br />one, and I also get a strong feeling that it's not really worth the<br />churn.<br /><br />                         Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
